# Product Development Rules

- Start from the user problem and target workflow, not from components.
- For every feature, identify user goal, success criteria, risks, and edge cases.
- Treat prototype scope separately from production scope.
- Always define acceptance criteria before implementation.
- Surface open questions explicitly instead of guessing silently.
- Prefer smaller, testable increments over broad feature generation.
